//annotations overview - component scanning
  1.what are java annotations: 1)special lables/markers added to java classes
                               2)provide meta-data about the class
                               3)processed at compile time or run-time for special processing
  2.development process: 1)enable component scanning in spring config file
                         2)add the @component annotation to your java classes
                         3)retrieve bean from spring container
